  "text": "with the first term vanishing due to (3.30) and the second vanishing due to the constrained nature of C µνρM . The terms inside the bracket are the \"undetermined terms\" O µν M of [CITATION_1] . Equation (3.31) ensures that the three-form potentials do not appear in the E 6 EFT action of [CITATION_2] , nor in the duality relation (3.22) . In [CITATION_3] , this leads to an ambiguity in the \"integrated\" form of this duality relation between certain components of F µν and H µνρ . Here, as we have access to the fully covariant field strengths, we instead assume the duality relation holds without the derivative:",
